Based on my search through the frontend directory, I found the wallet manager implementation scattered across multiple files. Here's a comprehensive report of the wallet manager system:

## Wallet Manager Implementation - File Locations and Code Analysis

### 1. **Main Implementation Location**
- **File**: `/root/frontend/index.html` (lines 4297-4970)
- **File**: `/root/frontend/js/moonyetis-slots.js` (lines 192-500)
- **File**: `/root/temp/deployment-package/frontend/test-wallet-complete.html` (complete standalone implementation)

### 2. **Core Wallet Manager Classes**

#### A. **BlockchainIntegration Class** (`/root/frontend/index.html` lines 4297-4931)
```javascript
class BlockchainIntegration {
    constructor() {
        this.apiBase = '/api/blockchain';
        this.connectedWallet = null;
        this.walletType = null;
        this.accountInfo = null;
        this.isConnecting = false;
        this.gameSession = null;
        this.pendingTransactions = new Map();
    }

    // Core wallet detection method
    getWalletProvider(walletType) {
        switch (walletType) {
            case 'unisat':
                return window.unisat;
            case 'okx':
                return window.okxwallet?.bitcoin;
            default:
                return null;
        }
    }

    // Main wallet connection method
    async connectWallet(walletType) {
        if (this.isConnecting) return { success: false, error: 'Connection in progress' };

        try {
            this.isConnecting = true;

            if (walletType === 'demo') {
                return this.connectDemoMode();
            }

            const walletProvider = this.getWalletProvider(walletType);
            if (!walletProvider) {
                throw new Error(`${walletType} wallet not installed`);
            }

            const result = await this.requestWalletConnection(walletType, walletProvider);
            // ... authentication and session setup
        } catch (error) {
            // ... error handling
        }
    }

    // Wallet connection request handler
    async requestWalletConnection(walletType, provider) {
        try {
            const accounts = await provider.requestAccounts();
            const address = accounts[0];
            const publicKey = await provider.getPublicKey();

            const message = `Connect to MoonYetis Slots\nAddress: ${address}\nTimestamp: ${Date.now()}`;
            const signature = await provider.signMessage(message);

            return {
                success: true,
                address: address,
                publicKey: publicKey,
                signature: signature
            };
        } catch (error) {
            return { success: false, error: error.message };
        }
    }
}
```

#### B. **WalletManager Wrapper Class** (`/root/frontend/index.html` lines 4934-4967)
```javascript
class WalletManager {
    constructor() {
        this.blockchain = new BlockchainIntegration();
    }

    async connectWallet(walletType) {
        return await this.blockchain.connectWallet(walletType);
    }

    async placeBet(amount) {
        const result = await this.blockchain.playSlotRound(amount);
        if (result.success) {
            return { success: true, txHash: result.roundId || 'demo_tx_' + Date.now() };
        }
        return result;
    }

    async processPayout(amount) {
        return { success: true, txHash: 'auto_payout_' + Date.now() };
    }

    disconnectWallet() {
        this.blockchain.disconnectWallet();
    }

    get connectedWallet() {
        return this.blockchain.connectedWallet;
    }

    get balance() {
        return gameState.balance;
    }
}
```

### 3. **Wallet Integration Functions** (`/root/frontend/js/moonyetis-slots.js`)

#### A. **Wallet Detection and Connection**
```javascript
